				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-3458007/scp-3064#post-3681232</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 13 Jan 2018 17:08:07 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Tzuvembi</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3187602</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Thank you for pointing out the typo, I've corrected it now! And glad you liked the Ugarit prayer - I dug through some of the archaeological literature on the Hurrian Songs to try and get the right 'feel' for how translated Assyrian is usually presented.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-3458007#post-3679409</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-3458007/scp-3064#post-3679409</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 12 Jan 2018 06:24:53 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Litfried</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1391439</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>A very nice SCP, well-rounded and with a good level of detail. I like the multiple instances appearing throughout history; the lyrics to the Ugarit prayer are also very cool and have the right historical feel (to me, a non-expert). This is not the flashiest SCP but it ought be much more highly regarded, in my opinion.</p> <p>One small criticism: is the final collapsible meant to read ‘Partial TranslatiXXXXf SCP-3064-6/A‘ when opened?</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
