					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-3458007#post-3579472</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-3458007/scp-3064#post-3579472</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sun, 27 Aug 2017 09:50:49 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Tzuvembi</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3187602</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Thank you! It's an idea I first had years ago when noticing that listening to something stupid like Caramelldansen in conjunction with thinking about/watching something that scared me tended to make me less scared of that thing thereafter. Originally it was just going to be the music box but I thought making the SCP the melody itself would be more interesting.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-3458007#post-3579372</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-3458007/scp-3064#post-3579372</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sun, 27 Aug 2017 04:26:16 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>fieldstone</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1436137</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I honestly would not have thought that &quot;fight song that makes you brave&quot; had enough substance to work as an SCP, but you pulled it off. I really like how it explores the effects of a simple anomaly in-depth, instead of just cranking up the violence or something, and the story of <em>Sugar Sugar Sweet Fear</em> really drew me in. +1.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
